    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re "Victims' Families Fight for Mercy" (news article, Feb. 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re "Victims' Families Fight for Mercy" (news article, Feb. 1):</p>
        <p>While I sympathize with those who have lost loved ones to violent crime, their inclination toward forgiveness cannot be measured against the growing majority of Americans who hold the opposing view.</p>
        <p>It is understandable how, in the midst of suffering, some victims' families may not want to contribute to the suffering of others. However, we who have not  yet become victims, whose pain has not yet been reduced to statistics, must be protected.</p>
        <p>Until our criminal justice system can work to safeguard us from repeat violent offenders, it is not only ethical but essential that the death penalty be applied with conviction and dispatch.</p>
        <p>MARK LIPSKY New York, Feb. 1, 1996</p>
      </block>
